accessibility.text: Our original thought was to implement an application that would use processed data from an image and generate sound.
This proved to be quite complicated and two very different images could produce the same audio.

Understanding the challenges from processing images and creating audio, we attempted to create audio based on abstract art created the user.  This however faced it’s own challenges.  Including how to associate synths with drawing, what order to play and how would looping work to actually create a sound.
After understanding the challenges of trying to interpret visuals in order to produce audio, we decided to use visuals as a way to understand what audio will be played.
